   THE BACKGROUND PROCESSING OPTION GENERATES JOB STATEMENTS AND JCL FOR
   EXECUTING PROCESSING PROGRAMS.  GENERATED JCL IS PLACED IN A TEMPORAR
   DATASET UNTIL A REQUEST IS MADE FOR THE JOB TO BE SUBMITTED OR CANCEL

   BEGINNING USERS OF SPF SHOULD REVIEW THE FIRST THREE TOPICS BELOW.
   THE LAST TOPIC MAY BE USEFUL FOR THE MORE ADVANCED USER.

 THE FOLLOWING TOPICS ARE PRESENTED IN SEQUENCE, OR MAY BE SELECTED BY N
    &1$- BACKGROUND SELECTION MENU
    &2$- PROCESSING PROGRAM JCL
    &3$- BACKGROUND JOB SUBMISSION
    &4$- BYPASSING THE BACKGROUND SELECTION MENU
<ACTION>
1 SELECT CHAR(36) CURSOR;
2 SELECT CHAR(8) LIST(     1,     2,     3,     4)
               RETURN(HJOB01,HJOB02,HJOB03,HJOB04);
3 * CHAR(8) INIT('TS      ');
4 * CHAR(8) INIT('HJOB1   ');
5 * CHAR(8) INIT('HJOB01  ');
<END>
